{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fbd8ac7e-d51e-4928-849f-40db8737cc8b","content":"Here's a quick reference:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"185fc88f-08ac-4f42-9d36-fa3ab15845de","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":302,"requestId":"4823:4804C:76D2FC:89396A:69FBE748"},"id":"538b892c-14e1-4f81-8de2-ebfb37648117","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:13:50.913Z","parentId":"bee010f0-14e8-4b78-8f17-4e965077ba92"}
